| 5 | 🟠 Important | `GET /api/settings` | Rate limit thresholds exposed |
| 6 | 🟠 Important | `POST /api/auth/login` + `register` | Timing oracle for email enumeration |
| 7 | 🟠 Important | `core/scan_limits.py` | Redis outage = auth rate limiting disabled |
| 8 | 🟠 Important | `POST /api/leads/scan` | Unbounded `keywords` array → CPU DoS |
| 9 | 🟠 Important | `PATCH /api/leads/{lead_id}/status` | Misleading CSRF dep — future dev trap |
| 10 | 🟡 Minor | `core/auth_cookies.py` | Cookie TTL > JWT TTL mismatch |
| 11 | 🟡 Minor | `POST /api/auth/register` | `full_name` not sanitized → stored XSS |
| 12 | 🟡 Minor | `core/supabase_client.py` | Admin client returned by default name |
| 13 | 🟡 Minor | `core/config.py` | unverified JWT role decode |
| 14 | 🟡 Minor | `reddit_service.py` | Unbounded comment cache per instance |
| 15 | 🟡 Minor | `GET /api/leads/export.csv` | Missing `X-Content-Type-Options` + CSV injection |
| 16 | 🟡 Minor | `core/auth_cookies.py` | `SameSite=lax` instead of `strict` |
| 17 | 🟡 Minor | `core/client_ip.py` | "unknown" shared IP bucket → DoS |

---

## Priority Order for Fixes

1. **Fix #3 first** — Subreddit injection is an active input validation gap exploitable right now
2. **Fix #8** — Unbounded keywords array is a DoS vector on every scan
3. **Fix #2** — Make CSRF unconditional on logout
4. **Fix #1** — Document/test that RLS is never bypassed via admin client fallback
5. **Fix #6** — Add a fixed `asyncio.sleep` jitter to auth endpoints
6. **Fix #11** — Sanitize `full_name` before storing
7. **Fix #5 + #4** — Strip internal config from health/settings responses
8. Remaining minors can be addressed in a single hardening PR
